records.addlTxt: 1:06 PM Defendant Kenneth A Frohn appeared by video. Alex Kito appears with DE from the PD office.   Attorney Emily Nelson appeared by video for State of Wisconsin.  Case is set for an Init App Sept 6, this hearing was requested by the PD office.  DE was sitting on a child support warrant and a Sawyer County warrant.  DE is currently on a $500.00 cash bond, State asks that bond continue.  Atty Kito requests a breakout room with DE. 1:23 pm back on the record.  Atty Kito argues bond, states DE has a cash job awaiting him, DE informs Atty he missed court in Sawyer as he had no transportation, had the warrant for one year which indicates he stayed out of trouble, argues for a sign bond.  The court will deny the bond motion, will order cash bond remain.  Court will order that the complaint be filed within 48 hours.  Adj 1:27pm.

2:16 PM Defendant Kenneth A Frohn appeared by video.  Attorney Emily Nelson in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls the case. DE wishes to have counsel appointed. DE has contacted the PD office concerning his Sawyer County warrant, DE states he is eligible for services. DE is to call on Rusk case also. State asks for $500.00 cash bond, absolute sobriety, do not operate a MV without a valid operating privilege. 

Court will set a $500.00 cash bond, Defendant is not to consume or possess alcohol.  Do not enter premises where alcohol is primary business, any bars taverns or liquor stores or any other establishment where the primary purpose is the sale of alcohol. No possession/consumption or use of illegal or illicit drugs, or any substance intended to use to alter mental state or mood.  Not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  No possession of medications not prescribed to you by a physician.  Do not operate a motor vehicle without a valid operating privilege.
